            "body": "> local base_on_attach = vim.lsp.config.eslint.on_attach -- fails on this line\n\n`vim.lsp.config.eslint.on_attach` returns a function for me. If it isn't for you, then nvim-lspconfig is not on your 'runtimepath' or there is an order-of-operations problem. I can't say for sure because I don't know how you've arranged your config files (and I'm not going to debug your config for you).\n\nJust a guess, but I assume that lazy sets 'runtimepath' later in the startup process, but wherever you are referencing `vim.lsp.config.eslint` is executing before that happens.",
